ANTONIO CONTE has rubbished rumours Eden Hazard will join Real Madrid.<br />
<br />
Blues boss Conte says the Chelsea star is happy at Stamford Bridge. &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t know, I am repeating the same thing,&rdquo; said Conte. &ldquo;I am focused on the present. Now it's important for my players to be focused on the present, not look too far forward. It's dangerous. Eden is a Chelsea player, we are happy with him, he is happy with us and see no problems with him.&rdquo; But Conte has revealed he hasn't discussed the rumours with the winger, claiming his focus is on the Blues' fixtures. &ldquo;No, it is not important to speak about this,&rdquo; Conte added. &ldquo;I like to speak to him about this season, the importance of this game. He missed Stoke, we have to check his form and I hope he shows tomorrow great things, to play great football. I like to talk about this.&rdquo;
